text: Rev - You know better and are too smart to counter with a straw man fallacy. thoughtco.com/straw-man-fall… Nite
To some, like myself, Rev, the border wall is a physical representation of the cultural and racial insults President Trump has spewed since his campaign announcement.

A physical wall is also a wasteful expenditure of taxpayer dollars, stomps on property rights of private landowners, has unknown environmental and wildlife ramifications and stifles economic activity and drain money that’s badly needed to create jobs, fund schools, and repair

beaten-up roads. There is currently a record-low levels of northbound apprehensions, For example, El Paso is the safest city in the country, and not a single terrorist or terror plot that has used our connection with Mexico to do us harm.

Border crossing rates have gone down for twenty straight years, according to U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP), part of a long-term trend that started long before Trump came into office. Irrational, obsessive focus on the border will prevent us from stopping threats where

they really exist and will waste precious resources that are needed elsewhere. The future of border security lies in manpower and smart technology, not medieval defenses. The wall is nothing more than a campaign slogan/promise - with little justification imho.

No mention whatsoever about the workers that are suffering from the shutdown of government. @realdonaldtrump the vast majority are outside Washington DC Paany other president not consulted by miller would have included them in the conversation.
Rev - Are you aware that all @realdonaldtrump is doing is returning to what was taken away by the Administration (regarding DACA protection)?
